  "prompt_text": "Implement a trie data structure. When is a trie more efficient than a hash table?",
  "response_text": "I will now implement a basic Trie data structure in Python and explain when it is more efficient than a hash table.\n\nFirst, let's define the Trie class:\n\n```python\nclass TrieNode:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.children = {}\n        self.is_end_of_word = False\n\nclass Trie:\n    def __init__(self):\n        self.root = TrieNode()\n\n    def insert(self, word):\n        node = self.root\n        for char in word:\n            if char not in node.children:\n                node.children[char] = TrieNode()\n            node = node.children[char]\n        node.is_end_of_word = True\n\n    def search(self, word):\n        node = self.root\n        for char in word:\n            if char not in node.children:\n                return False\n            node = node.children[char]\n        return node.is_end_of_word\n\n    def starts_with(self, prefix):\n        node = self.root\n        for char in prefix:\n            if char not in node.children:\n                return False\n            node = node.children[char]\n        return True\n```\n\nNow, let's discuss when a Trie is more efficient than a hash table:\n\n1. **Space Efficiency**: A Trie can be more space-efficient when dealing with strings of similar prefixes. This is because a Trie stores common prefixes in a shared way, reducing the overall space complexity. In contrast, a hash table stores each word as a separate key-value pair, which can lead to a higher space complexity.\n\n2. **Time Efficiency**: A Trie can be more time-efficient for operations like prefix search and autocomplete, as it only requires traversing the Trie structure to find matching prefixes or words. In a hash table, these operations would require iterating over all keys, which can be slower.\n\n3. **Order Preservation**: A Trie preserves the order of the keys (words), which can be useful in certain applications. A hash table does not preserve the order of its keys.\n\n---VCP RATINGS---\nA (Analytical Precisio